On the most recent episode of the @theallinpod, legendary start-up investor @DavidSacks said:   “The way I saw Excel was the long tail of use cases that hadn’t yet moved into a dedicated SaaS app yet…  If you wanted to be a SaaS founder and you’re trying to come up with ideas, find some really complicated excel spreadsheet that’s used across so many different businesses. Just figure out if you can move that into a SaaS app…”  Enter @TryAssemble.  This morning, I met @EEsclusa, Co-Founder + Co-CEO of Assemble who walked me through the product which helps companies “make better compensation decisions” and in doing so, create a high-performance team culture.  The way companies have had to use spreadsheets to “manage” this process which can be overwhelming, ineffective etc at times, reminded me of exactly what David Sacks described.  A phenomenal challenge / opportunity space to build a business.  No doubt, Enrique and the Assemble team are building something special and in doing so, they just might reinvent the way companies attract, retain and cultivate talented people.  What has been and always will be, every company’s #1 asset.  Check them out.

Hey, founder, Why are you feeling low today?    The million-dollar idea does not excite you anymore.    Simple things look like an uphill task. Motivation is at an all-time low:  We all face ups and downs in our start-up journey.    But why? From my real experience, I could think of possible reasons.    Funding: Running low on funds can really impact a business, especially for committed founders. Competition: Standing out in a competitive business landscape can lead to discouragement among startup founders.  Personal Sacrifices: Starting and growing a business often involves personal sacrifices, leading to stress and burnout.  Setbacks: Despite planning, setbacks are inevitable and can be demoralizing for founders.  Burnout: Demanding startup responsibilities can lead to burnout, affecting motivation and well-being.    What to do: Talk to people you connect with.   Your friends, family, or mentors. Do not be tough on yourself.  You have it in you.   Give yourself a little time.  It is a long-haul game.   Your mental well-being comes first.

Talking about your ideas with people can be discouraging sometimes.  When we started working on our start-up idea, we talked to many people, shared our idea, and discussed about it. We wanted to gain some insights and feedback, and we got many.  A few of them were encouraging but mostly negative and discouraging.  Sometimes the very people we admired passed critical feedback that we would stop for a moment and think again. It disturbed our conviction to start our own company.  Over time, we started ignoring those people, we would of course listen to them but not really “take them seriously.”   We realized one thing, people who stand on the sidelines love to pass free advice.  But it’s super hard to stand in the arena. It’s scary to put yourself out there in the game.

✨Launching an AI Start-up in Canada through the Start-up Visa Program  Are you an AI enthusiast with a groundbreaking start-up idea? Canada beckons you with its thriving tech ecosystem and the Start-up Visa program. Designed to attract innovative minds, this program offers a gateway for AI entrepreneurs to establish their ventures and gain permanent residency. Let's delve into how you can launch your AI start-up in Canada and ride the wave of innovation.  Why Canada for Your AI Start-up? Canada's commitment to innovation and technology makes it an ideal destination for AI entrepreneurs. Cities like Toronto, Vancouver, and Montreal boast robust AI communities, research institutions, and supportive start-up ecosystems. The Start-up Visa program offers a fast track to Canadian permanent residency, unlocking a host of benefits for you and your venture.  Leveraging the Start-up Visa Program The Start-up Visa program connects you with designated organizations, venture capital firms, and angel investors. These entities recognize the potential of your AI venture and provide the necessary support, including funding, mentorship, and resources. This program paves your way to permanent residency, allowing you to focus on nurturing your AI start-up's growth.  Steps to Launching Your AI Start-up in Canada  1. Craft a Compelling Business Idea: Develop a unique and scalable AI concept that addresses real-world challenges. Whether it's healthcare, finance, or automation, your idea should showcase innovation and potential for impact.  2. Connect with Designated Organizations: Partner with a designated organization approved by the Canadian government. Their expertise and support enhance your business plan, increasing your chances of success.  3. Secure Funding: Venture capital firms and angel investors are keen on funding AI ventures. Present a strong business case highlighting your AI's unique selling points, market potential, and scalability.  4. Navigate the Visa Process: Collaborate with designated organizations to secure a Letter of Support. This document accelerates your visa application process and sets you on the path to permanent residency.  5. Leverage Canada's AI Ecosystem: Benefit from Canada's AI research hubs, tech meetups, and industry conferences. Networking here is invaluable for partnerships, collaborations, and staying updated on AI trends.  6. Drive Innovation: With access to funding and resources, focus on refining your AI technology. Continuous innovation will position your start-up as a game-changer in the industry. Here's how you could run it. If I wanted to launch an online start-up, I'd love such course and cohort.   "Startup Journey: From Idea to Launch in 5 Weeks"  Embark on an interactive, hands-on experience where you not only learn the ins and outs of launching a startup but actually put those learnings into action. This 5-week course is designed for budding entrepreneurs ready to turn their ideas into realities.  Format & Pricing:  Mode: Cohort, Live weekly calls (recorded for those who can't attend). Duration: 5 weeks. Group Size: Limited to 6-8 participants for personalized attention. Investment: $150 - $200 total. Course Breakdown:  Call 1: "Laying the Foundation" Dive into the methodology behind your startup process (literally your twitter thread). Explore the process of ideation and brainstorming. Assignment: Everyone submit their  startup idea on a platform you develop / host (or just google docs).  Call 2: "Pitch Perfect" Participants pitch their startup ideas (60-second limit) and receive real-time feedback and insights from you and participants. Then you teach them to set goals for the coming week, alongside with your own process. Keep objectives achievable.  Call 3: "Gaining Traction" from now it's a peer-group for accountability and support. Showcase the deliverables of your startup, and ask them to show theirs.  Engage in peer discussions: pitch progress, Q&A sessions, and collaborative problem-solving. Special focus on marketing strategies to drive website traffic.  Call 4: "Maintaining Momentum"Continue with the interactive show-and-tell sessions. Engage in peer group feedback, delve deeper into each startup's journey, and overcome challenges together.  Call 5: "Ready, Set, Launch!"Finalize strategies, business models, and marketing plans. Celebrate the progress of each startup. Discuss next steps and post-course support.  Turn your startup dream into a reality, step by step, with guidance and a supportive community.  Ideally they all have a product launch after 5 weeks, and they can profit from your exposure!

Entrepreneurs Wanted: Canada's Start-up Visa Program Awaits Your Innovation  Are you an aspiring entrepreneur with bold ideas and a drive to innovate? Canada's Start-up Visa Program is your invitation to turn your dreams into reality in one of the world's most thriving and diverse business landscapes.  Innovate on a Global Stage: Canada has long been celebrated for its inclusive society, robust economy, and welcoming business environment. The Start-up Visa Program leverages these strengths to attract international talent. If you possess a unique business concept, cutting-edge technology, or a game-changing solution, Canada eagerly awaits your contribution to its dynamic economy.  A Pathway to Permanent Residency: The Start-up Visa Program not only offers a platform to realize your entrepreneurial vision but also paves a pathway to permanent residency. Your success as an entrepreneur can lead to becoming a permanent resident of Canada, with all the rights, benefits, and opportunities this status entails for you and your family.  Connecting with Canadian Expertise: One of the program's distinct advantages is the opportunity to connect with Canadian business experts and mentors. The expertise they provide can prove invaluable in refining your business model, navigating the local market, and achieving long-term success. Networking with these professionals enhances your knowledge and opens doors to potential partners, investors, and collaborators.  Access to Funding: Financing is often a critical factor in the success of any start-up. Canada's Start-up Visa Program brings you closer to an array of funding options, including venture capital firms, angel investors, and governmental support programs. These resources can provide the financial backing necessary to drive your business forward.  Thriving in a Diverse Ecosystem: Canada's multicultural society is reflected in its business landscape, creating an environment where diverse perspectives and ideas flourish. As an entrepreneur, this ecosystem allows you to tap into a rich talent pool, collaborate with people from various backgrounds, and develop products and services that resonate on a global scale.  A Foundation for Innovation: The Start-up Visa Program recognizes that innovation isn't confined to a single sector or industry. Whether you're developing groundbreaking technology, disrupting traditional models, or bringing a fresh approach to an existing market, Canada's open and inclusive business culture supports your journey to success.  Steps to Success: To embark on this transformative journey, start by developing a comprehensive business plan that outlines your concept, market potential, and growth strategy. Partner with a designated organization that aligns with your vision, and secure a Letter of Support that validates your business idea and enhances your application.  A Bright Future Awaits: Canada's Start-up Visa Program is more than an immigration pathway – it's an opportunity to contribute to a nation known for its innovation, diversity, and resilience. By embracing this program, you're joining a community of entrepreneurs who are shaping the future of industries, creating jobs, and driving economic growth.  If you're ready to take your entrepreneurial aspirations to the next level, Canada's Start-up Visa Program is your gateway to innovation, growth, and the chance to call a country renowned for its quality of life and business opportunities your new home. Your ideas are the catalyst for change, and Canada is eager to welcome you into its vibrant and dynamic business landscape. Seize the opportunity, bring your innovation to life, and contribute to Canada's entrepreneurial journey. Your future awaits!  🌐 Connect with us!
